SIMPLE: weathered
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weathered
<hw>Weath"ered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Made sloping, so as to throw off water; <as>as,
a <ex>weathered</ex> cornice or window sill</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Having the surface altered in
color, texture, or composition, or the edges rounded off by exposure to
the elements.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weather-fend</ent>⟦br⟧
